05/10/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonia's deputy prime minister in charge of EU integration, Radmila Sekerincka, announced Monday (4 October) that the translated European Commission (EC) questionnaire has been delivered to all ministries. She noted that the document includes 1,922 sections with over 3,000 questions, most of which are directed to the ministries of economy, finance and labour. The government is to submit its answers to the EC by 31 January as part of its bid to receive official EU candidate status. (Dnevnik - 05/10/04; A1 TV, Makfax - 04/10/04)
